&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Strategic Workforce Business Partner&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leeds Health and Wellbeing Strategy 2016-2021&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;LEEDS HEALTH AND CARE &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ONE WORKFORCE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to work as the Strategic Workforce Business Partner for Health and Care across the city of Leeds. In an innovative partnership model, Health and Care organisations across Leeds have come together to develop and deliver the Leeds Health and Wellbeing Strategy. As part of a small team, working in collaboration with the Leeds Health and Care Academy, this role is responsible for developing and driving forward system-wide projects relating to workforce planning, education, training, recruitment, engagement, retention, and progression. Providing professional insight and analysis, the post-holder will maintain strategic focus on the ‘One Workforce’ goal, and will work with senior leaders and HR&amp;OD professionals across organisational boundaries to design, facilitate and deliver effective workforce strategies which realise the city’s shared ambitions. Expertise in strategic workforce management is essential, as is excellent relationship management, but critically the post holder will share the city’s passion to transform health and care for our citizens.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information, please contact Kate O’Connell, Director of Leeds Strategic Workforce and Health &amp; Care Academy on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;LHCA@leeds.gov.uk&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Closing Date: 23rd November&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Selection Process: Provisionally 9th and 10th December &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
